üü¶ EPIC 1 ‚Äî Hardware Allocation Process

(User-facing entry: ‚ÄúCollect My Equipment‚Äù)

Goal

Allow a technician to deliver hardware to a collaborator only based on existing requests, using a controlled and guided workflow.

‚∏ª

US1 ‚Äî Start Hardware Allocation Process from visit management

As a technician
I want to start the Hardware Allocation Process when managing a visitor
So that I can deliver equipment requested by the collaborator

Acceptance Criteria
	‚Ä¢	The process can be started only when the visit type is Collect My Equipment
	‚Ä¢	The process name displayed is Hardware Allocation Process
	‚Ä¢	The process starts when the technician clicks Manage
	‚Ä¢	The workflow uses a stepper layout consistent with Return Hardware

‚∏ª

US2 ‚Äî Display pending hardware requests for the collaborator

As a technician
I want to see all pending hardware requests for the collaborator
So that I know what equipment must be delivered

Acceptance Criteria
	‚Ä¢	All open and deliverable requests for the collaborator are displayed
	‚Ä¢	Each request shows:
	‚Ä¢	Requested equipment type (PC, Mac, Smartphone, Accessory, etc.)
	‚Ä¢	Category / level if applicable (e.g. PC Premium)
	‚Ä¢	Request reference
	‚Ä¢	Requests are read-only at this stage

‚∏ª

US3 ‚Äî Handle case where no request exists

As a technician
I want to be informed when no request exists
So that I can requalify or cancel the visit

Acceptance Criteria
	‚Ä¢	A clear message indicates that no request exists
	‚Ä¢	The technician can:
	‚Ä¢	Requalify the visit
	‚Ä¢	Cancel the visit
	‚Ä¢	The allocation process cannot continue without a request

‚∏ª

US4 ‚Äî Select a request to fulfill

